The paper discusses security and authorization issues in services oriented grids, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also mentions the use of PKIX and X.509 certificates, which are commonly used in distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the implementation of a State Police Information Grid (SPIG), which involves distributed systems and networking (cs.Distributed) and potentially involves issues related to cyber security (cs.CY).
